The Fighting Pit is the dark mirror to the Crossroads Meeting. Where one tests emotional bonds, the other tests command through strength. Neither is "wrong" - they represent different philosophies of leadership in a darkening world.

The Pit Master serves as a dark reflection of what the player might become - someone who served the dragon and failed, now reduced to testing others. His revelation that he was the dragon's "first champion" plants seeds for the larger narrative.

The betrayal mechanics reinforce that mercenary loyalty is always conditional. The crowd favor system shows how brutality gains quick approval but may cost you later. The final choice between single combat and mass battle tests whether you trust your leadership or your personal prowess.

Most importantly, the "unified" path remains possible but difficult - proving you can blend both companions and mercenaries into a cohesive force. This is the hardest path but offers the greatest rewards.
